<P><PB N="141" REF="028644_0149_0FDA2B4A297A9F30">
By this table of experiments it appears that some fall short,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Art. 67.</NOTE> and others exceed the maximum, and all agree as near as can be expected in an af|fair where so many different circumstances are concerned; therefore we may conclude the max|im to be true.</P>
<P>MAX. II. That the expence of the water be|ing the same, the effect will be nearly as the height of the virtual or effective head.</P>
<P>This also will appear by comparing the con|tents of columns 4, 8 and 10 in any of the sets of experiments.</P>
