<P>The effect therefore of No. 24, compared with No. 2, is less than according to the present max|im in the ratio of 49: 50.</P>
<P>MAX. III. that the quantity of water expend|ed being the same, the effect is nearly as the square root of its velocity.</P>
<P>This will appear by comparing the contents of columns 3, 8 and 10, in any set of experiments; <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> for
