<P><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">, clean it over several times, in order <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> out all the garlic that can be got out of the machinery, (which is easily done if you <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> a wheat elevator well fixed, as directed <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">. 94. pl. IX.) then chop or half grind it, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> will break the garlic, (it being softer <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> the wheat) the moisture of which, will so
