<P>Suppose we choose 66 cogs in the big cog-wheel and 48 in the little one, and 5 rounds in the wallower, and 15 in the trundle.</P>
<P>Then, to find the revo|lutions of the stone for one of the water-wheel, multiply the cog-wheel, together, and the wallow|er and trundle together, and divide one product by the other, and it will quote be answer, 8 168/375, not quite <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> revolutions instead of 9.</P>
