<P>Thus we have completed the calculations for one mill, with a 16 feet overshot water-wheel, and stones 4 1-2 feet diameter. By the same rules we may calculate for wheels of all sizes from 12 to 30 feet, and stones from 4 to 6 feet diameter, and may form tables that may be of great use to many, even to master workmen that understand calculating well in dispatching of business, in laying out work for their apprentices and other hands, getting out timber, &amp;c. but more especially <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> those who are not learned in arithmetic sufficient to calculate, I being from long ex|perience highly sensible of the need of such a <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">ble, have therefore undertaken the arduous <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">.</P>
