<P>For particulars see what is written over the head of each table. Table I. is to suit a 4 feet stone, table II. a 4 1-2, table III. a 5 feet, and table IV. a 5 1-2 feet stone.</P>
<P>N. B. If the stones should be an inch or two bigger or less than those above described, make use of the table that comes nearest to it, and likewise for the water-wheels. For further particulars see draughting mills.</P>
<DIV4 TYPE="directions">
